gomodel:SYNGO_4981  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: Ultrastructures of synapses imaged using EM are not altered between wildtype and DJ-1 (PARK7) knockout neurons.\n\nFigure 3: Primary cultured cortical neurons from wildtype and DJ-1 knockout mice were transfected with vGlut1-pHluorin (its fluorescence can be used to monitor endocytosed vesicles). DJ-1 knockout resulted in significant defects of SV endocytosis, which was completely rescued upon reexpression of wildtype DJ-1. Authors summarised these results as; \"Based on these findings, we concluded that DJ-1 plays an important role in SV endocytosis during and after neural activity.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"DJ-1 KO mice were kindly provided by U. J. Kang at the Department of Neurology, University of Chicago, Chicago, IL\" PMID:15799973" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4981" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

